seng202.team1.Model

Class BikeTrip

  • java.lang.Object
    • seng202.team1.Model.DataPoint
      • seng202.team1.Model.BikeTrip
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BikeTrip
extends DataPoint
implements java.io.Serializable
    Bike Trip data class. If birthYear = -1, this is a flag which means the data is not available. Gender will be m (male), f (female), or u (unknown).
    See Also:

      • getDuration

        public ContextualLength getDuration()
        Returns the duration of the trip, contextualised. Either in seconds, minutes, hours, or days (rounded down). This means that a trip that took 1 day, 23 hours, 59 minutes, 59 seconds will be "1 day". E.g. "20 minutes", "3 days" (without the quotes).
        Returns:
        the contextual duration of the trip

      • getDistance

        public ContextualLength getDistance()
        Returns the distance of the trip, contextualised. Either in m (meters) or km (kilometres). Rounded to the nearest 3 digits of precision. E.g. "236 m", "73.7 km" (without the quotes). Currently coded for trips 1m - 999km.
        Returns:
        the contextualised distance of the trip
